4 - OSIRIS SCRIPT NOTES

osiris has support to play mp3 files and wav files. the way i have it setup
is to use mpg123 and wavplay. i have included my copies of these programs
because they wont output any garbage. the files are in ~/osiris/sound
if you need any help with setting up the mp3 or wav players, just msg me
and ill help you. the flags listed when u type /mp3 aren't the only
available flags, they are just most commonly used. if you want the full list
of flags, from your shell prompt type '/dir/to/mpg123' and it'll show u all
the available flags. before msging me make sure u join #BitchX and see if im
there, theres some lamer that likes to use my nick (plk6@mars.its.yale.edu)
so dont confuse the 2 of us. my hostname is always *tor-cn.concentric.net
some of the stuff in this script might be confusing at first, but like i
said, if u need help..msg me. if you find bugs and/or have ideas, put them
in a file called yournick.osiris.bugs or yournick.osiris.ideas

you can set ansi in your realname by using the cparse color codes.
if youre either using /config to set your realname or just using /realname
the way to set it with ansi is like this:

/realname %Wl%Be%be%Kt           <-.- this will make your realname say 'leet'
                                   `- with a white to blue to high black fade

using /config:

do /config, then at the menu..hit the character for realname [n], and you'll
see this:

realname? 

at that prompt u use the cparse color codes just like in /realname.

cparse color code reference: 

%w == white              %W == bright white
%r == red                %R == bright red
%b == blue               %B == bright blue
%c == cyan               %C == bright cyan
%g == green              %G == bright green
%p == magenta/purple     %P == bright magenta/purple
%m == magenta/purple     %M == bright magenta/purple
%y == brown              %Y == yellow


